<object id="GUID-0BB38D32-0AE1-4CC4-93EB-F4635CC3E4AE" class="- topic/object "><desc class="- topic/desc "><p class="- topic/p ">Cool down printheads </p></desc><param name="testid" value="046015" class="- topic/param "/><param name="target" value="NIL" class="- topic/param "/><param name="axmodule" value="None" class="- topic/param "/></object> 
</p></section><section id="GUID-1156E15C-FA11-42F7-80CE-F9823F371FA9" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Function</title><p class="- topic/p ">Cool down the printheads to a temperature of 40 °C (104 °F) as fast as possible. The print surface fans are used to generate extra cooling air. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Close the top cover and remove any media from the print surface before you start the test. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The test cools down the printheads 30 minutes faster than a regular cool down. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The test ends automatically when the temperature is reached. 
